MOESER v. VON WILMOWSKY. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. June 11, 1909.) Action by George Moeser against Felix F. Von Wilmowsky.

With tide case has been consolidated in this court cases bearing titles as follows: Patrick Gallagher v. Mary Gallagher; William Carter v. Edwin Hess et al.; Same v. Italian Swiss Colony et al.; Same v. John Holl et al.; Same v. Pneumatic Whitewash Co.

No opinions. Motions granted, unless appellants have appeals ready for October term. Orders filed.
